<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">New Class Talk Discussions</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=358936" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
<p><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/055114.html">Rogue Talk Dicussion</a></p>
<p>
Hello again.</p>
<p>
This will be the thread for discussion about the rogue class. The idea is to look at the things that need to be changed to make the class 'balanced'. With that as the primary goal, I am still interested in hearing about bugs and other such things. But, primarily, I want to talk about balance.</p>
<p>
My take on the rogue is pretty similar to that of the warrior. They are pretty well balanced. Obviously with EverQuest as a primarily player vs. environment game, some of the things that thieves traditionally do are not really part of the package. That's why, in EverQuest, they are titled rogues.</p>
<p>
Again, I have had little time (actually, no time at all) to do research on rogue concerns before starting this thread. So please be as detailed as you need to be to get your point across. But, at the same time, please remember that this thread will get long. So being concise and readable is important too.</p>
<p>
I do want to report one thing that we have already discovered internally about rogues that is broken and will be fixed when we make these changes. Yes, it is a nerf, but not in the true sense of the word.</p>
<p>
In the old days, NPCs had a limited size to their hate-list (basically the way that they track who they are angry at). In those days, evade would just drop you to the bottom of that list. Recently we increased the size of that list dramatically. This allows us to do a lot more with NPCs. But evade was never changed to reflect this, so it still drops you to the bottom of the hate-list. Essentially, this allows a rogue to do significant damage to an opponent, and then with the use of evade, become less 'hated' than someone that has done no damage to the NPC at all, but just has a somewhat negative faction with that NPC and is standing someplace on the other side of the zone. The rogue can then beat the NPC up with impunity. Basically, evade is far too useful for avoiding aggro from an NPC, and we're going to change it to be more in line with its original function.</p>
<p>
I wanted to let you know that at the outset. Please don't make it the focus of this thread. It’s certainly something we should talk about. But there are certainly other things that are worth discussion as well.</p>
<p>
So let's hear what you think.</p>
<p>
Alan</p>
<p><hr size="1"><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/055491.html">Paladin Talk Dicussion</a> *Link Updated</p>
<p>
By now you may already have seen some of the things that we plan to do with the paladin class in the hopes of adjusting their balance. Those changes came about, mostly, from our folks reading the threads about the other hybrids and reading those about paladins that were started in preparation for this thread. Feel free to discuss those changes as well, though I think they are all very much in line with what is needed for the paladin.</p>
<p>
Here's a list that I stole from Everlore… I was too lazy to actually look them up (but this list seems accurate):</p>
<p>
a) Add Endure Magic spell at level 30<br>
b) Add Resist Magic at 55<br>
c) Move Guard spell from 49 to 39<br>
d) Move Armor of Faith from 53 to 49<br>
e) New level 53 paladin spell, Divine Glory, clone of divine strength but 100 hp instead of 200<br>
f) New level 59 spell, Celestial Cleansing 110 hp healdot per tick, for 4 ticks. 1.5 second casting time. Recast time 30 secs.<br>
g) Defense skill cap made exactly same as warriors</p>
<p>
So let's start the discussion. Please be detailed when explaining things. But at the same time, please be precise. I really don't need your background as a player, or detailed examples of gameplay (unless they are needed to explain a game mechanic). These threads get long, and anything that you folks can do to cut down the amount of text or increase the readability of the posts is appreciated.</p>
<p>
And remember, we're primarily discussing 'balance' here. Bugs and such are fine to point out, but they are not the main reason we are here.</p>
<p>
So let's hear what you have to say.</p>
<p>
Alan</p>
<p><hr size="1"><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/055118.html">Ranger Talk Dicussion</a></p>
<p>
Hi all.</p>
<p>
You may already have seen a list of some of the things that we are already testing as changes for the ranger class. Essentially, we are adjusting the level at which some of their spells are attained to make them more in line with their power.</p>
<p>
Here is a list that I, once again, stole from Everlore because I'm lazy and because it seems accurate:</p>
<p>
a) Add Endure Cold at 22<br>
b) Add Skin Like Nature at 59<br>
c) Add FireFist at 22<br>
d) Move Bramblecoat from 49 to 39<br>
e) Add Spikecoat at 49<br>
f) Add resist cold at 55<br>
g) Add Panic Animal at 22<br>
i) Offense and weapons skill made identical to warriors</p>
<p>
Let's talk about these changes and others that might be needed to 'balance' rangers.</p>
<p>
Keep in mind that I primarily want to talk about 'balance' here. I'll certainly list any bugs that you would like to see addressed, but the focus should be balance. And please be concise when responding. These threads will get very long, and it helps me to be able to read all the responses if they are to the point.</p>
<p>
Let's hear what you have to say.</p>
<p>
Alan</p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
